description.narrative: UNICEF supported close to 70% of Community Adolescents Treatment Supporters (CATS) and 96% of Young Mentor Mothers (YMMs) to continue to provide virtual support to adolescents living with HIV (ALHIV) and pregnant and breastfeeding adolescent mothers respectively and their communities, which assisted with treatment adherence especially during COVID-19.A total of 10,391 (6,235 female and 4,156 male) adolescents received information on HIV, sexual and reproductive health, gender-based violence and COVID 19, through UNICEF-supported community radio programmes and U-Report (messaging via SMS) facilitated by trained young U-Reporters and radio presenters. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2022
